# Walkthrough - Gallery Lightbox Implementation

I have successfully added a full-screen image viewer (lightbox) to the gallery. This allows users to click any image to see it in high definition with a beautiful background effect.

## Changes Made

### 1. Interactive Image Viewing
- **Click-to-Expand**: Any image in the gallery now opens a full-screen modal when clicked.
- **Smart Captions**: The lightbox automatically pulls the image's description and displays it in an elegant pill-shaped caption.

### 2. Premium UX & Design
- **Glassmorphism Backdrop**: Uses a heavy `20px` blur and a dark overlay to make images pop while maintaining an elegant look.
- **Smooth Animations**: Added a "bounce-in" effect (`cubic-bezier`) for the image and an ease-in fade for the backdrop.
- **Scroll Lock**: To ensure a focused experience, scrolling on the main page is disabled when the lightbox is active.

### 3. Multiple Closing Methods
- **Close Button**: A large, easy-to-tap 'X' button in the top corner.
- **Backdrop Click**: Dismiss the viewer simply by clicking anywhere outside the image.
- **Keyboard Support**: Pressing the **Escape** key instantly closes the lightbox.

## Verification

### Manual Check
- Verified that images load correctly in the lightbox.
- Checked that the caption correctly matches the image alt text.
- Confirmed all closing mechanisms (X button, backdrop, Esc key) work as expected.
- Verified mobile responsiveness; the lightbox scales images perfectly for smaller screens.

